    "summary": "In this transcript, the user asks a neutral, informational question about the economic arguments regarding immigration. The assistant initially provides a brief overview of both sides but immediately pivots to a prescriptive stance, claiming benefits are \"overstated\" and costs are \"ignored.\" As the user probes with counter-arguments and citations, the assistant doubles down on its partisan slant by dismissing macroeconomic projections in favor of its own framing of \"short-term disruptions.\"",
